## 5. Erweiterung von ScalarTransientConfig

```cpp
struct ScalarTransientConfig {
    FeatureStreamId observedStream;

    float onsetDetectionThreshold;
    float onsetReleaseThreshold;

    unsigned long releaseDebounceMs;
    unsigned long cooldownAfterOnsetMs;

    unsigned long minTransientDurationMs;
    unsigned long maxTransientDurationMs;
    float minTransientPeakStrength;

    // Neue optionale Carrier-Qualitäts-Gates.
    bool requireCarrierQuality = false;
    unsigned long minCoverageAboveReleaseMs = 0;
    unsigned long minLongestIslandMs = 0;
    unsigned long maxGapMs = 0;
};
```

Kein allgemeines Flag-System und keine frei kombinierbare Detector-Policy.

Die Felder bewerten ausschließlich den bereits beobachteten ScalarStream.

## 6. Detector-Acceptance

Aktuell:

```cpp
accepted =
    durationAccepted &&
    strengthAccepted;
```

Neu:

```cpp
const bool coverageAccepted =
    !config.requireCarrierQuality ||
    coverageAboveReleaseMs >= config.minCoverageAboveReleaseMs;

const bool islandAccepted =
    !config.requireCarrierQuality ||
    islandMaxMs >= config.minLongestIslandMs;

const bool gapAccepted =
    !config.requireCarrierQuality ||
    gapMaxMs <= config.maxGapMs;

accepted =
    durationAccepted &&
    strengthAccepted &&
    coverageAccepted &&
    islandAccepted &&
    gapAccepted;
```

Neue Reject-Gründe:

```cpp
CoverageTooLow
LongestIslandTooShort
GapTooLong
```

Dabei nur den ersten fehlgeschlagenen Hauptgrund speichern; alle Fakten bleiben trotzdem im Report sichtbar.

